com.gunnarhoffman.converters

Class DistanceConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gunnarhoffman.converters.DistanceConverter
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImperialDistanceConverter, MetricDistanceConverter

    public abstract class DistanceConverter
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows for the conversion between three length/distance type systems. Metric, Imperial, and Astronomical. Each system ranges in size respectivly from Mirometers to Kilometers, Inches to Miles, and Astronomical Units to Parsecs. The conversion between these systems is only lossy if division causes a never terminating decimal, in that case it will halt at the hundreth deciaml place.
    Author:
    Gunnar Hoffman

      • setUnit

        public final DistanceConverter setUnit(java.math.BigDecimal unit)

        Sets the raw unit value in the underlying data source for this class.

        This method is final to protect the constructor from undefined behavior should this class be extended.

        In the event a negative number is passed into this function a runtime exception of the type InvalidParameterException will be thrown. All static methods on this object indirectly call this method and therefor can also throw this exception.

        Parameters:
        number - The number of units to operate over.
        Returns:
        An instance of this class containing the unit number.
